Subject:    What happens between 2:00 and 2:15?
From:       <a href="?a=95837783700008&r=1&w=2">Craig Partridge &lt;craig () loki ! bbn ! com&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198604">1986-04-14 20:02:41</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026682&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026682&q=raw">body</a>]</b>


Hello,

    We recently started having problems our domain servers crashing
frequently.  We'd come in mornings and discover they were down.
Recently we started using a program which checked every 15minutes to
see if the server was up, and if not, restarted it.  The program writes
to a log and we have noticed a funny phenomena.  The server gets
restarted only some days, and always at 2:15 A.M. EST.  It looks
suspiciously like some server is sending bomb packets to us at that
hour.  Does anyone on this list restart/fiddle with their servers
at that hour?

Craig Partridge
CSNET Technical Staff

P.S.  The days we had to restart our server over the past week were:
Monday the 7th, Tue the 8th, Thu the 10th and Monday the 14th.  All
at 2:15!

